      "rationale": "Four-level mesh refinement study performed on the screw shank and rod-screw interface. Stiffness QoI changed 1.4% from medium (0.4 mm element edge) to fine (0.2 mm); yield force changed 1.1%. Production mesh uses medium density with Richardson extrapolation correction applied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver residual < 1e-6 for all load steps; energy balance error < 0.1%.",
      "rationale": "Sparse direct solver (SPARSE) used for linear steps; Newton-Raphson with line search for nonlinear post-yield steps. Force residual converged to < 5e-7 in all 11 construct simulations. Energy balance error < 0.05% confirmed via post-processing script."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent peer review of model setup by analyst not involved in primary model development; checklist documented.",
      "rationale": "Secondary analyst reviewed boundary conditions, material assignments, contact definitions, and load application against the F1717 fixture specification. Twelve checklist items verified; two minor corrections (friction coefficient assignment) identified and corrected prior to production runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification that continuum elasto-plastic constitutive model with isotropic hardening is appropriate for Ti-6Al-4V screw under monotonic quasi-static bending.",
      "rationale": "Ramberg-Osgood elasto-plastic model with isotropic hardening selected for Ti-6Al-4V. Strain rates in F1717 quasi-static test (<0.01 s-1) preclude rate-dependent effects. Microstructural anisotropy of wrought bar stock assessed as negligible for macro-scale bending response. Model form consistent with FDA guidance on metallic implant FEA."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from coupon testing of same lot material; geometric inputs from CMM measurement of production screws.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus (114 GPa), yield strength (880 MPa), and tangent modulus derived from tensile coupon tests on same Ti-6Al-4V bar stock (n=5 coupons). Screw geometry inputs from CMM measurements of three production screws per lot. Uncertainty quantification performed on E, sigma_y, and thread pitch diameter using Monte Carlo sampling (5000 draws); output variance attributed to combined material and geometric uncertainty. Note: a formal sensitivity analysis identifying the relative contribution of individual inputs to output variance is planned for a subsequent revision of this assessment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N >= 10 constructs from production lots; traceability of samples to manufacturing records confirmed.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs assembled from production-representative screws and rods (same lot as commercial product). Certificate of conformance and dimensional inspection records available for all 11 constructs. Samples distributed across two independent laboratories to assess inter-laboratory variability."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span clinically relevant range of loading rates and environmental conditions.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single crosshead displacement rate (5 mm/min) per ASTM F1717. Physiological saline environment not employed; ambient lab conditions used. Single test condition limits generalizability; this factor is below required level. Accepted under risk-informed rationale that quasi-static monotonic loading is the governing failure mode for this COU."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA input parameters (geometry, material, boundary conditions) demonstrably equivalent to experimental specimen parameters.",
      "rationale": "CMM-measured geometry used directly in FEA; material properties from same lot coupons. Boundary conditions replicate F1717 fixture geometry (upper and lower fixture blocks modeled as rigid bodies with measured pin-hole clearances). Torque preload on set screw modeled via pretension element calibrated to torque-angle data from assembly records."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric E/uval < 1.96 for all QoIs; percent difference < 10%.",
      "rationale": "Three QoIs compared: stiffness (E/uval=1.41, diff=6.2%), yield force (E/uval=1.63, diff=8.7%), force at 40 mm (E/uval=1.78, diff=9.1%). All within acceptance bounds. Validation uncertainty uval computed from experimental repeatability (inter-lab COV 4.1%) and numerical uncertainty (mesh + solver combined 1.6%)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly correspond to regulatory submission claims and clinical failure modes.",
      "rationale": "Stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in the 510(k) predicate comparison and align with ASTM F1717 reporting requirements. Yield force maps directly to implant fatigue initiation risk; 40 mm displacement force characterizes post-yield reserve capacity relevant to intraoperative overload scenarios."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation scenario geometry, loading, and material are representative of the COU device and intended use environment.",
      "rationale": "Validation uses the identical non-cannulated 7.5 mm screw geometry and Ti-6Al-4V material as the submission device. ASTM F1717 fixture represents standardized worst-case bending loading accepted by FDA as representative of in vivo spinal loads. Two-laboratory design increases confidence in result generalizability. COU is regulatory submission support, and validation directly addresses the submission claim."
    }
