    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve factors meet or exceed required levels. One factor (Test conditions) is at Gradation 2 against a required Gradation 3; accepted under risk-informed rationale that quasi-static monotonic loading is the governing failure mode and that single-condition testing is consistent with ASTM F1717 normative requirements. All three QoIs satisfy the pre-specified acceptance criterion (E/uval < 1.96; percent difference < 10%). Uncertainty quantification has been performed; sensitivity analysis to rank individual input drivers is planned but not yet complete. Overall credibility is sufficient to support the intended regulatory submission use.",
